  "steps": [
    {
      "title": "1",
      "body": "Cut the sides of the cart to size.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/fe8ffc82fd13c436.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "2",
      "body": "Cut the top of the storage cart to size.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/a99adc5154e3e8da.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "3",
      "body": "Using 1 1/4\" pocket screws and wood glue, attach the top through the pocket holes on the inside of the sides of the cabinet.\nMake sure the top of the cabinet overhangs 3/4\".",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/5bd4fcc4f2a46b6b.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "4",
      "body": "Attach the bottom to the sides of the cabinet using 1 1/4\" pocket screws and wood glue.\nPocket holes can face up or down, either way they won't be visible.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/81bddebb677278af.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "5",
      "body": "Cut all the drawer pieces to size.\nRun a 1/4\" x 1/4\" groove on the inside of the drawer box pieces.\nThe groove should start 1/2\" up from the bottom of the drawer pieces.\nYou can use a track saw or a table saw for this!",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/045ecf639da7ef29.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "6",
      "body": "Drill pocket holes only on the front side of the front & back pieces of the drawer box pieces.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/948294611d344ec5.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "7",
      "body": "Put the drawer box together using wood glue and 1 1/4\" pocket screws.\nThe pocket holed pieces should face out and back. This way they wont be visible once the drawer front is put on.\nSlide the plywood bottom into the grooves in the drawer, you can add a little glue in the grooves for more durability.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/541d0b424d62828c.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "8",
      "body": "Install the drawer slides using the dimensions in the image.\nThe drawer slide on the bottom should sit 1\" from the bottom of the cabinet to the bottom of the drawer slides.\nAll the other drawer slides should be 3.656\" from the bottom of one slide to the bottom of the next slide.\nThis is where a piece of scrap wood cut to size will come in handy!\nInstall the drawer boxes using the same method you installed the drawer slides.\nUse a scrap piece of wood to space them out!",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/235ded7f8f64b673.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "9",
      "body": "You can either cut out a handle for the drawer fronts with a jigsaw or you can just attach your favorite hardware.\nAfter you've done that, screw the drawer fronts onto the drawer boxes from the inside of the drawers.\nMake sure they are spaced evenly and that the last drawer front is flush with the bottom of the cabinet.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/70d3990941715ad5.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "10",
      "body": "Paint, attach your casters and you're done!",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/1df10a7f769d540f.webp"
    }
  ],
